						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near a palmyra tree on the hillock in the village.</p>						

						<p>Harihara II, 1388 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated Śaka 1310, Vibhava, Mēsha 1, Sunday. The details are irregular, the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponding to 1388 A.D., March 26 when the week-day was Thursday.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift to land and money income for feeding eight <hi rend="italic">brāhmaṇas</hi> and for other purposes (details lost) by Sōmayadēva Kalutūṟa of Hariharapura and another (name lost) who was the son of Narasaṁha of Kauṇḍinya-gōtra, when <hi rend="bold">Maṅgarasa</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Maṅgalūru-rājya.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
